Service Engineer/Technician (SVC-Fisher/201204/01/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00003180
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Sep 12 2012
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Outage management coordination (customer contact, repair evaluations, safety, replacement parts and documentation).
Conduct On-site Flow scanner Diagnostics/FIELDVUE testing, diagnostic testing data interpretation and recommendation.
Generate report for customers on outages and diagnostics.
Provide support with emphasis on unique situations; conduct valve repair work both in-house and at customers’ site.
Take initiative to sell maintenance contracts to customers.
Work with the business unit on customer's complaint and derive solutions to solve issues that customers are facing.
Requirements:
Diploma or Higher NITEC in Electrical Engineering with at least 3 years of related experience, preferably in instrumentation and process industry.
Aggressive in building a strong rapport with customers, vendors, and internal associates.
A team player with strong problem solving skills and task oriented.
Able to travel on short notice and assist Customer Service Specialist in processing orders when required.
Experience in a service operation or maintenance (mechanical and electrical) is a plus.
Possess a Class 3 driving license would be preferred.